Overview
--------

libfronius is a free software library to send/receive data to/from
Fronius inverters which implement Fronius' serial communication protocol.
This library can use a serial port or an Ethernet connection.

The description of the serial communication protocol is available e.g.
in the manual to the Fronius Interface Card easy[1].

The license of libfronius is LGPL v2.1 and the licence of programs in
tests directory is GPL v3.

The documentation is available under the Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike
License 3.0 (Unported) (http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/).

The library is written in C and designed to run on Linux.


Installation
------------

The shell commands are ``./autogen.sh; ./configure; make; make install``.


Report a Bug
------------

To report a bug, you can:
 * fill a bug report on the issue tracker
   http://github.com/mhei/libfronius/issues
 * or send an email to mhei@heimpold.de


